cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about coreference resolution, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and its related fields. The paper also proposes a generative, unsupervised ranking model, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses metrics to evaluate the performance of the proposed model, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with entity resolution, which is a common task in the field of network embedding, making cs.NE (Networks and Networking) another possible category.
